03/01/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The OSCE Presence in Albania and the ODIHR voiced satisfaction Thursday (30 December) with the commitment expressed by two main political forces to passing the revised elections law. The ruling Socialists and the main opposition Democrats agreed that the amendments should be passed in January and that electoral zones should be redrawn in February. 
On Friday meanwhile, Albanian Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami met with US Ambassador to Tirana Marcie Ries. They discussed bilateral relations and Albania's progress in the Euro-Atlantic integration process. (ATA - 31/12/04; ATA - 30/12/04)
